snippet.textDisplay:
آج رنگ ہے ری ماں رنگ ہے ری
میرے محبوب کے گھر رنگ ہے ری
Keeping the beautiful legacy of Qawwali alive, started by great Sufi Saint Ameer Khusro when he wrote the piece for his beloved Khuawaja Nizam uddin Aulia, a wonderful rendition by Ustaad Rahat Fateh Ali Khan and the great late Amjad Sabri. 
They can kill the Sabri, but cannot finish the legacy!

snippet.textDisplay: this is the last performance of the great Amjad Sabri and Rahat Fateh Ali Khan together. After hearing the soulful call of the maestros, ever the hearts of staunch atheists like me goes soft. This is an opportunity for us to think what is wrong with the subcontinent. If two great perfomers of Pakistan can render a great kalam of Amir Khusrau written in pure purvi Hindi, soulfully and blissfully, why cant we coexist? why will propagators of love like Amjad Sabri face death at the hands of religious fanatics? why should there always be a threat of war between two neighbouring countries that share common cultural heritage? what is the problem with us? cant be simply understand peace?
